</title>
<subSubSection id="7068DB4C42023E5EBF174DA2E4833728" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="F68DEB3C6BBCC26FEC0F855816420370" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">
Unterscheidet sich von der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="9B5A40CB17A2DD1F93A3E27C8D3D1EE4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Myosotis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0C4BE7E6A22BD5CD745BE8193ABC3357" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Myosotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, S. 72, durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="343AF0EA5A83089D3AC2B7709A380B2C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">
Jede 
<normalizedToken id="283BDC425A8E7BC24B2EF1B36F5DDF46" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Bluete</normalizedToken>
mit Tragblatt; 
<normalizedToken id="AE8BC6CB18A413D0A6ADFB11AE2F7635" originalValue="Oberfläche" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Oberflaeche</normalizedToken>
der 
<normalizedToken id="4579779824221D82058FE7D1D3E88022" originalValue="Teilfrüchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Teilfruechte</normalizedToken>
mindestens am Rande borstig, stachelig oder 
<normalizedToken id="A36621FAE2E87FA64966F2767064BB5A" originalValue="gezähnt" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">gezaehnt</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E46268F8F360CC291776783501415581" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="FCEBF3870BAC9364C3F11F408903ADC5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94DFAB30CC04D136B578F8A47DD91497" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Eritrichium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="20A7910BFF7A07820FBA25BBC4E065D7" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="EA25EF1D339F9E12C32DC77E6FF5625E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">30 Arten, die in den Gebirgen Eurasiens und Nordamerikas Vorkommen.</emphasis>
Die 4 mit unserer 
<taxonomicName id="BDEF8E9264C56C151737C427DD827E5D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanum">
<emphasis id="1CE68565B9CAE39563493DF9AAC77209" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">E. nanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
verwandten Arten (
<taxonomicName id="252A2060EFC333B6F2BA6C22A28D3A79" authority="Simonkai in den Karpaten" authorityName="Simonkai in den Karpaten" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jankae">
<emphasis id="E0FC689422E0DA91FE68E4FD735860B7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">E. Jankae</emphasis>
Simonkai in den Karpaten
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4D15C5A717578BF23E744F3C816F4D61" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="null" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosum">
<emphasis id="337F48A002530664D58EDDAB9A4E276D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">E. villosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[Ledeb.] Bunge in asiatischen Gebirgen und 2 nordamerikanische Arten) wurden von Lechner-Pock (1956) dargestellt (
<normalizedToken id="EAF63D14180B6C393EB4EFA8A8733CD5" originalValue="Schlüssel" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">Schluessel</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="265BB8C9D197FA8B755AAE7BC77D3C52" originalValue="ausführliche" pageId="null" pageNumber="81">ausfuehrliche</normalizedToken>
Diagnosen, sehr viele Fundortsangaben, Verbreitungskarten, Standorte).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
